claim.claim-text:
1. A method for laser trimming resistors, the method comprising:
measuring a resistance value for resistors of a set of resistors that are formed during manufacture of a circuit platform;
sorting the resistors into one or more bins based on the measured resistance values and target resistance values associated with each resistor;
assigning a laser trim file to bins based on a predictive trim formulation, each laser trim file defining a set of configuration parameters for a laser drill to conform each resistor with their respective target value; and
using the laser drill to trim the resistors within each bin in accordance with the laser trim file assigned to that bin;
wherein the laser trim file further defines a drill pattern on the resistor to form a planar channel within the resistor.

7. The method of claim 1, further comprising:
measuring a resistance value of each trimmed resistor associated with a particular bin;
adjusting the laser trim file associated with the particular bin based on a distribution of the measured resistance values of the trimmed resistors within the particular bin;
displaying a distribution of the trimmed resistance values to assess performance of the laser drill file associated with the particular bin; and
displaying a distribution of the measured resistance values associated with each bin to assess performance of an underlying passive component formation process;
wherein the configuration parameters defined by the laser trim file include at least a spot size and power level for the laser drill, and the laser trim file includes at least a step size, an overlap factor and number of feed steps over the resistor to form the planar channel.

20. The system of claim 18, wherein:
the configuration parameters defined by the laser trim file include at least a spot size and power level for the laser drill;
the laser trim file includes at least a step size, an overlap factor and number of feed steps over the resistor to form the planar channel;
the tester is further configured to measure a resistance value of each trimmed resistor associated with a particular bin;
the laser trim application is further configured to adjust the laser trim file associated with the particular bin based on a distribution of the measured resistance values of the trimmed resistors within the particular bin;
the laser trim application is further configured to display a distribution of the trimmed resistance values to assess performance of the laser drill file associated with the particular bin; and
the laser trim application is further configured to display a distribution of the measured resistance values associated with each bin to assess performance of an underlying passive component formation process.

23. A computer program product comprising:
a computer usable medium having computer readable program code embodied therein, the computer readable program code comprising:
computer readable program code that receives a resistance value for resistors of a set of resistors that are formed during manufacture of a circuit platform;
computer readable program code that sorts the resistors into one or more bins based on the measured resistance values and target resistance values associated with each resistor;
computer readable program code that assigns a laser trim file to each bin based on a predictive trim formulation, each laser trim file defining a set of configuration parameters for a laser drill to conform each resistor with their respective target value; and
computer readable program code that outputs, for uploading to the laser drill, a file having assignment of the respective resistors to respective laser trim files.

27. The computer program product of claim 23, further comprising:
computer readable program code that receives a resistance value of each trimmed resistor associated with a particular bin;
computer readable program code that adjusts the laser trim file associated with the particular bin based on a distribution of the measured resistance values of the trimmed resistors within the particular bin;
computer readable program code that displays a distribution of the trimmed resistance values to assess performance of the laser drill file associated with the particular bin; and
computer readable program code that displays a distribution of the measured resistance values associated with each bin to assess performance of an underlying passive component formation process;
wherein the configuration parameters defined by the laser trim file include at least a spot size and power level for the laser drill, and the laser trim file includes at least a step size, an overlap factor and number of feed steps over the resistor to form the planar channel.

28. A computer software tool for use in laser trimming comprising:
a library of laser trim files, each laser trim file defining a set of configuration parameters for a laser drill to conform resistors with their respective target values;
a computer usable medium having computer readable program code embodied therein, the computer readable program code comprising:
computer readable program code that receives a resistance value for resistors of a set of resistors that are formed during manufacture of a circuit platform;
computer readable program code that sorts the resistors into one or more bins based on the measured resistance values and target resistance values associated with each resistor;
computer readable program code that assigns a laser trim file from the library to each bin based on a predictive trim formulation; and
computer readable program code that outputs, for uploading to the laser drill, a file having assignment of the respective resistors to respective laser trim files.
